{"word":"θεῖος","slug":"θεῖος","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b><el>ϑεῖος, α, ον</el></b> [<el><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:θεός\">θεός</a></el>] ‘associated with deity’<b><p class=\"pp3\"/>—<pp>a.</pp></b> as <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ adj.\">adj.</a> <b>divine <a href='B:680 1:3'>2 Pt 1:3f</a>.<p class=\"pp3\"/>—<pp>b.</pp></b> as noun <el>τὸ <a class=\"S\" href=\"S:θεῖον\">θεῖον</a></el> ‘divine being, deity’: <el>νομίζειν χρυσῷ</el>... <el>τὸ <a class=\"S\" href=\"S:θεῖον\">θεῖον</a> εἶναι ὅμοιον</el> consider what is divine to be akin to gold, etc. <b><a href='B:510 17:29'>Ac 17:29</a>;</b> <el>λειτουργεῖν τὸ <a class=\"S\" href=\"S:θεῖον\">θεῖον</a></el> to administer what has to do with deity <b><a href='B:630 1:9'>Tit 1:9</a> <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ v.l.\">v.l.</a></b> <center id=\"nav_bottom\"> <a id=\"left_arrow\" href=\"S:θεῖον\">&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;</a> <a id=\"bottom_home\" href=\"S:#1.Table of Contents\">&emsp;&emsp;</a> <a id=\"right_arrow\" href=\"S:θειότης\">&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;</a> </center> "}]}